FOR CHANNEL 10 NEWS,

02:09.607 --> 02:12.567
HERE'S RIPTIDE ROGER PELTON
WITH THE SURF REPORT.

02:12.697 --> 02:16.788
-RIPTIDE: THE SURF SUCKS!
BUT THERE'S STILL SOME GENIUSES

02:16.919 --> 02:20.357
OUT HERE WAITING
FOR A SWELL. WHY?

02:20.488 --> 02:22.620
BECAUSE THEY DON'T
WATCH ME IN THE MORNING!

02:22.751 --> 02:26.885
-[ROCK MUSIC]

02:30.933 --> 02:32.500
DON'T COME TO THE
BEACH FOR THE SURF,

02:32.630 --> 02:36.808
COME FOR THE RUSH! [CHEERS]

02:37.766 --> 02:39.898
RUSH HOUR TRAFFIC ON
PCH, THERE IS NONE,

02:40.029 --> 02:42.597
THIS ISN'T A RUSH HOUR, I
DON'T GET UP THAT EARLY.

02:43.511 --> 02:46.601
EVERYONE KNOWS YOU DON'T
WATCH FOR THE SURF REPORT,

02:46.731 --> 02:48.777
YOU DON'T WATCH FOR
THE TRAFFIC REPORT,

02:48.907 --> 02:52.607
YOU WATCH FOR THE
LIFEGUARD REPORT! [LAUGHS]

02:52.737 --> 02:56.959
-[ROCK MUSIC]

03:00.092 --> 03:02.269
THAT'S THE ONLY REASON
YOU CHOOSE A BEACH.

03:02.399 --> 03:05.620
FORGET THE SURF, YOU CAN
TAN IN YOUR BACKYARD,

03:05.750 --> 03:08.188
YOU CHOOSE THE BEACH
WITH THE LIFEGUARD

03:08.318 --> 03:11.408
THAT FULFILLS YOUR
FANTASY OF A LIFEGUARD!

03:11.539 --> 03:13.845
WHATEVER IT IS, THAT'S
WHERE YOU WANNA BE.

03:21.462 --> 03:23.507
OOH! THERE IS THE
LIFEGUARD THAT HAS

03:23.638 --> 03:26.815
STIMULATED MY
FANCY THIS SUMMER!

03:26.945 --> 03:27.816
DONNA...

03:35.519 --> 03:37.826
OW! THAT WOMAN IS SO HOT!

03:37.956 --> 03:39.915
I WOULD DIE AND GO
TO HADES JUST TO HAVE

03:40.045 --> 03:42.309
DONNA GIVE ME MOUTH TO
MOUTH, I'M SERIOUS, I WOULD.

03:42.439 --> 03:45.529
LET'S TAKE A LOOK AT WHO'S
TRUCK SHE'S GETTING IN.

03:49.968 --> 03:53.885
AH, LOOKS LIKE J.D.,
ALIAS JACK DARIUS,

03:54.016 --> 03:57.498
ALIAS THE DAYTONA PIER
KILLER, WHO'S EQUALLY HOT.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.501
IF I WAS A WOMAN,
I WOULD ABSOLUTELY

04:00.631 --> 04:03.547
PLANT MY BOOTY AT THE
BASE OF HIS TOWER.

04:06.507 --> 04:08.291
AH, AND THERE'S NEWMIE!

04:10.032 --> 04:11.425
NEWMIE, THIS GUY'S
ALWAYS WORKIN' OUT,

04:11.555 --> 04:13.862
I GUESS IT WORKS
FOR HIM, THIS YUTZ

04:13.992 --> 04:16.952
IS GOING WITH A GIRL
WITH THE MOST LUSCIOUS

04:17.082 --> 04:21.086
LIPS I HAVE EVER SEEN ON
A WOMAN IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

04:31.880 --> 04:34.926
-RIPTIDE: AND THERE IT
IS, THE HIVE, THE HAVEN,

04:35.057 --> 04:36.450
BAYWATCH LIFE
GUARD HEADQUARTERS,

04:36.580 --> 04:39.409
WHERE THE TANNED AND
TONED BODIES PUT ON

04:39.540 --> 04:41.672
THOSE LUSCIOUS RED
BATHING SUITS, OH!

04:44.153 --> 04:46.938
-GET THAT HELICOPTER
OUT OF HERE!

04:47.069 --> 04:49.027
-RIPTIDE: AH, THERE'S
LIEUTENANT TAYLOR WALSH!

04:49.158 --> 04:52.335
I JUST GO WEAK FOR
A WOMAN IN UNIFORM,

04:52.466 --> 04:55.947
YOU GOTTA LOVE THAT
RED, FIERY HAIR.

04:59.081 --> 05:01.866
WELL, LOOK AT THE EXPRESSIONS,
THAT WOMAN WANTS ME.

05:01.997 --> 05:06.958
SHE'S JUST TOO TERRIFIED
OF MY RAW, ANIMAL SEXUALITY

05:07.089 --> 05:08.960
TO LET IT SHOW, SO IT
COMES OUT AS ANGER.

05:09.091 --> 05:11.615
[LAUGHS] OOH! DON'T
YOU LOVE THE WAY

05:11.746 --> 05:13.487
SHE MOVES HER CAN
AROUND LIKE THAT?

05:13.617 --> 05:15.750
MOVE IT, HONEY! YEAH!

05:16.533 --> 05:17.926
LORDY, LORDY, LORDY!

05:21.016 --> 05:22.278
-HEY LOOK, IT'S TAYLOR!

05:23.061 --> 05:24.367
-I HATE THIS GUY.

05:24.498 --> 05:26.064
-WHY? HE'S FUNNY.

05:28.240 --> 05:29.807
-RIPTIDE: NO ONE'S
ACTUALLY SEEN THE GUY.

05:29.938 --> 05:32.506
RUMOR HAS IT
THAT TAYLOR WANTS

05:32.636 --> 05:34.159
EVERYONE TO THINK
SHE'S ENGAGED, SO--

05:34.290 --> 05:36.466
-WHAT IS TAYLOR
DOING OUT THERE?

05:37.728 --> 05:39.643
I TOLD EVERYBODY TO
IGNORE THAT IDIOT.

05:40.514 --> 05:42.124
-RIPTIDE: YOU'D
THINK THESE LIFEGUARDS

05:42.254 --> 05:43.995
WOULD BE MORE
WORRIED ABOUT RIPTIDE

05:44.126 --> 05:47.129
IN THE SURF THAN
RIPTIDE ROGER PELTON.

05:48.217 --> 05:49.958
UH OH, I KNEW HE'D SHOW UP!

05:50.088 --> 05:53.396
CAPTAIN MITCH BUCHANNON!

05:53.527 --> 05:54.876
-COME ON INSIDE!

05:55.006 --> 05:56.399
-NO!

05:56.530 --> 05:57.705
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
NO? COME ON INSIDE,

05:57.835 --> 05:58.706
YOU'RE PLAYING RIGHT
INTO HIS HANDS.

05:59.446 --> 06:00.969
-THIS JUST SOUNDS
FREAKY TO ME.

06:01.099 --> 06:04.538
MITCH, A CAPTAIN. AS
LEGENDARY FOR SAVING LIVES

06:04.668 --> 06:06.496
AND BREAKING HEARTS, BUT
I UNDERSTAND HE'S READY

06:06.627 --> 06:09.151
TO SETTLE DOWN, SO THOSE
OF YOU LOOKING TO LAND

06:09.281 --> 06:12.981
LIFEGUARD NUMERO UNO, SEND
YOUR MARRIAGE PROPOSALS

06:13.111 --> 06:16.027
TO MITCH BUCHANNON, CARE
OF BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

06:16.158 --> 06:17.551
PICTURES AND
RESUMES, OF COURSE.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.163
-I'M NOT BACKING
DOWN IN FRONT OF

06:21.293 --> 06:23.818
100,000 PEOPLE
WATCHING ON TELEVISION.

06:26.168 --> 06:27.430
-NEWS DISPATCH: CHOPPER
10, PLEASE RESPOND TO A

06:27.561 --> 06:28.953
THREE VEHICLE
ACCIDENT ON HIGHWAY 1,

06:29.084 --> 06:30.607
NORTH OF YOUR LOCATION.

06:30.738 --> 06:32.130
-WE JUST GOT A REPORT OF
A THREE CAR PILEUP ON PCH.

06:32.261 --> 06:35.003
I KNOW THE ONE THING ALL
OF YOU LOVE MORE THAN

06:35.133 --> 06:37.658
LIFEGUARD GOSSIP, IT'S
CAR WRECK CARNAGE.

06:37.788 --> 06:40.051
I CAN'T LOOK, LET ME SEE,
CAN'T LOOK, LET ME SEE.

06:40.182 --> 06:41.836
AND NO ONE GETS
YOU CLOSER TO THE

06:41.966 --> 06:46.971
CARNAGE THAN RIPTIDE
ROGER PELTON!

06:50.322 --> 06:52.890
-THERE. HE BLINKED FIRST.

06:53.021 --> 06:56.285
-TANNER, YOU CAN'T
LET BEING ON TELEVISION

06:56.416 --> 06:58.243
COME BETWEEN
YOU AND YOUR JOB.

06:58.374 --> 06:59.506
-HE'S TRASHED OUR
PROFESSIONAL IMAGE

06:59.636 --> 07:01.290
AS WELL AS
OUR PERSONAL LIVES.

07:01.421 --> 07:04.032
-I KNOW, AND HIS RATINGS
ARE GOING THROUGH THE ROOF.

07:04.162 --> 07:06.077
-SOMEBODY HERE IS
FEEDING HIM INFORMATION.

07:06.208 --> 07:07.818
WE HAVE A SPY AT
BAYWATCH, MITCH.

07:07.949 --> 07:10.517
WE GOTTA FIND OUT WHO
IT IS AND STOP THE LEAK.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.565
-HOME AGAIN, HOME AGAIN.

07:15.696 --> 07:17.524
-HEY, CODY, THANKS FOR
LETTIN' ME STAY HERE, MAN.

07:18.438 --> 07:21.223
DONNA WAS JUST WORRIED PEOPLE
MIGHT GET THE WRONG IDEA.

07:23.704 --> 07:25.793
-AS LONG AS RIPTIDE DOESN'T
START A RUMOR ABOUT US.

07:25.923 --> 07:27.229
-[J.D. LAUGHS]

07:28.839 --> 07:30.885
-NO, J.D., NOT THAT ROOM!

07:32.843 --> 07:34.889
THIS WAS STEPHANIE'S.

07:36.717 --> 07:38.109
CAROLINE MADE
ME SWEAR I'D LEAVE

07:38.240 --> 07:39.241
EVERYTHING THE WAY IT WAS.

07:40.285 --> 07:42.549
-J.D.: MY MOM DID THAT
WITH MY DAD'S WORKSHOP.

07:43.288 --> 07:44.681
IT ONLY MAKES THE
PAIN LAST LONGER.

07:44.812 --> 07:47.249
-YEAH, I KNOW,
BUT CAROLINE'S JUST

07:47.379 --> 07:49.207
NOT READY TO
LET IT GO YET.

07:51.209 --> 07:53.255
YOU CAN STAY IN HER ROOM 'TIL
SHE GETS BACK FROM NEW YORK.

07:53.385 --> 07:54.604
-YEAH, WHAT'S
HAPPENING WITH THAT?

07:54.735 --> 07:56.127
DID SHE GET THE PART?

07:56.258 --> 07:57.607
-I DON'T KNOW, SHE
WAS SUPPOSED TO CALL.

07:57.738 --> 07:59.740
HER AUDITION WAS
FIVE DAYS AGO, AND

07:59.870 --> 08:01.437
NO ONE'S HEARD
FROM HER SINCE.

08:59.103 --> 08:59.930
-[CAROLINE SCREAMS]

09:00.061 --> 09:01.279
-[J.D. SCREAMS]

09:02.411 --> 09:04.108
-CAROLINE? WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

09:04.239 --> 09:06.197
-WHAT AM I DOING HERE?
WHAT IS HE DOING HERE?

09:06.328 --> 09:09.244
-I'M SORRY I GRABBED
YOU! IT WAS A REFLEX!

09:09.853 --> 09:11.072
-CAROLINE, THIS IS J.D.

09:11.202 --> 09:12.769
-YEAH, WE JUST MET.

09:12.900 --> 09:15.076
-CODY: J.D.'S STILL
LOOKING FOR A PLACE TO LIVE,

09:15.206 --> 09:17.121
SO I SAID HE COULD CRASH
HERE 'TIL YOU GOT BACK.

09:17.252 --> 09:18.732
-WELL, TADA! I'M BACK.

09:19.341 --> 09:21.561
-CODY: WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL
ANYBODY YOU WERE COMING?

09:21.691 --> 09:23.214
HEY, HOW DID
SHANNA'S HOPE GO?

09:23.345 --> 09:24.433
-LOOK, I DON'T
WANT TO TALK ABOUT

09:24.564 --> 09:25.695
ANY OF THIS RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

09:25.826 --> 09:27.305
I JUST SPENT FIVE
DAYS ON A BUS,

09:27.436 --> 09:28.568
AND I'M REALLY TIRED,
AND I'M REALLY CRANKY!

09:28.698 --> 09:29.656
-CODY: WELL, WHY'D
YOU TAKE A BUS?

09:29.786 --> 09:31.092
YOU HAD A ROUND-TRIP FLIGHT.

09:31.222 --> 09:32.615
-LOOK, OKAY, I JUST
NEEDED SOME TIME

09:32.746 --> 09:34.095
TO GET MY THOUGHTS
TOGETHER, DECIDE WHAT

09:34.225 --> 09:35.575
I'M GONNA DO WITH MY
LIFE, MAYBE THAT'LL

09:35.705 --> 09:37.228
GIVE YOU AN IDEA HOW
MY AUDITION WENT.

09:38.795 --> 09:41.276
-WELL, ANYWAY, GLAD
TO HAVE YOU BACK.

09:41.406 --> 09:42.930
-LOOK, I MEAN,
WHY DON'T I GO OUT

09:43.060 --> 09:45.367
AND SLEEP ON THE COUCH?
IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

09:49.937 --> 09:52.330
-THERE. NOW WE'RE EVEN.

09:53.810 --> 09:55.116
TAKE THE PILLOW.

09:58.032 --> 09:59.729
-IF, UH--

09:59.860 --> 10:02.123
-NOPE! YOU KEEP IT. WE'LL
DISCUSS ALL THIS IN THE MORNING.

10:02.689 --> 10:04.299
-WE'LL BE QUIET,
WE WON'T WAKE YOU.

10:04.429 --> 10:07.607
-IT'S OKAY, WAKE ME.
I WANT TO GET BACK

10:07.737 --> 10:11.001
TO THE BEACH AS SOON
AS [YAWNS] POSSIBLE.

10:12.176 --> 10:13.613
-GOOD TO MEET YOU, CAROLINE.

10:19.880 --> 10:24.275
-[PLEASANT MUSIC]

10:30.455 --> 10:35.025
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

10:37.854 --> 10:40.465
-I CAN'T TELL FOR
SURE UNTIL I SEE

10:40.596 --> 10:42.250
THOSE INCREDIBLE
EYES OF HERS,

10:42.380 --> 10:47.342
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE CAROLINE
HOLDEN IS BACK ON THE BEACH!

10:48.386 --> 10:51.172
OH! FOR THE LOVE OF GOD!

10:52.564 --> 10:57.004
I WOULD PAWN MY SOUL TO BE
THE SAND BENEATH HER FEET!

10:57.134 --> 11:00.311
THAT HAIR FLOWING LIKE A
HORSE'S MANE... [INHALES]

11:00.442 --> 11:03.837
[LAUGHS] OH MAN,
WILL YOU LOOK AT HER?

11:03.967 --> 11:05.665
I THOUGHT SHE WOULD
BE TIRED, WIPED OUT

11:05.795 --> 11:07.362
AFTER FIVE DAYS ON A BUS.

11:07.492 --> 11:10.060
THAT'S NOT EVEN THE TIRING
PART, LISTEN TO THIS:

11:11.105 --> 11:13.716
CAROLINE CAME HOME LAST
NIGHT TO DISCOVER THAT

11:13.847 --> 11:15.849
J.D. HAD MOVED OUT
OF DONNA'S CONDO

11:15.979 --> 11:17.633
AND IN WITH CODY AND HER.

11:17.764 --> 11:20.810
I DON'T THINK DONNA
WOULD BE TOO THRILLED

11:20.941 --> 11:24.118
TO HEAR HOW CAROLINE
RIPPED THE BLANKET

11:24.248 --> 11:26.947
OFF OF J.D.,
CHECKED OUT HIS BOD,

11:27.077 --> 11:30.515
HE WAS WEARING CK'S,
BLACK, AND THE TWO OF THEM

11:30.646 --> 11:33.301
ENDED UP SLEEPING
IN THE SAME BED!

11:33.431 --> 11:35.869
WHAT WOULD DONNA SAY?

11:37.174 --> 11:39.002
-YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

11:39.133 --> 11:41.178
-THAT'S WHAT HE
SAID, THE SAME BED.

11:41.309 --> 11:44.704
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW, I JUST
CAN'T BELIEVE THAT J.D. AND...

11:45.792 --> 11:46.401
CAROLINE!

11:46.531 --> 11:47.141
-DONNA, HI!

11:47.271 --> 11:48.229
-HI!

11:48.359 --> 11:49.143
-OH, IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

11:49.273 --> 11:49.752
-CAROLINE: YOU TOO.

11:50.405 --> 11:51.972
HI. I'M CAROLINE HOLDEN.

11:52.102 --> 11:53.974
-LANI MCKENZIE, I'VE
HEARD SO MUCH ABOUT YOU!

11:54.104 --> 11:56.672
-REALLY? I HOPE IT WAS
ALL ABOUT MY VIRTUES.

11:56.803 --> 11:58.413
-WELL, SPEAKING
OF VIRTUES, I HEARD

11:58.543 --> 11:59.893
YOU MET J.D. LAST NIGHT.

12:00.023 --> 12:02.373
-OH, HE IS GORGEOUS.
WHAT IS HIS STORY?

12:02.504 --> 12:04.462
-I DON'T KNOW, BUT
I'M HOPING TO FIND OUT.

12:04.593 --> 12:06.682
-REALLY? WHAT'S HE LIKE?

12:06.813 --> 12:08.249
-YOU SHOULD KNOW.

12:08.379 --> 12:09.946
-YOU SLEPT IN THE SAME
BED WITH HIM LAST NIGHT.

12:10.077 --> 12:12.166
-WHAT? WHO TOLD YOU THAT?

12:12.296 --> 12:13.733
-RIPTIDE. ROGER PELTON.

12:13.863 --> 12:15.082
-CAROLINE: WHO'S HE?

12:15.212 --> 12:16.344
-HE'S A HELICOPTER
PILOT WHO DOES

12:16.474 --> 12:17.737
THE BEACH REPORT
FOR CHANNEL 10.

12:17.867 --> 12:19.564
-OH YEAH, I THINK
I SAW HIM OUTSIDE.

12:19.695 --> 12:21.523
-YOU DID, AND HE SAW YOU.

12:21.653 --> 12:23.003
-SAID YOU MADE HIM DROOL.

12:23.133 --> 12:24.656
-WHAT?

12:24.787 --> 12:26.049
-YOU SEE, HE ALSO DOES
THE LIFEGUARD REPORT.

12:26.180 --> 12:28.225
YOU KNOW, WHO'S
IN WHICH TOWER...

12:28.356 --> 12:29.966
-SO COME ON, IS IT TRUE?

12:30.097 --> 12:31.315
DID YOU AND J.D. SLEEP IN
THE SAME BED LAST NIGHT?

12:31.446 --> 12:33.883
-NO! WELL, NOT AT
THE SAME TIME...

12:34.014 --> 12:35.537
ALL RIGHT, HE WAS IN
MY BED WHEN I GOT HOME,

12:35.667 --> 12:37.017
BUT THEN HE
MOVED TO THE COUCH.

12:37.147 --> 12:38.888
WHO IS FEEDING THIS
GUY ALL THIS STUFF?

12:39.019 --> 12:40.760
-WELL, HE HAS A
SPY, IT'S AWFUL.

12:40.890 --> 12:43.066
-WHO DO YOU
THINK THE SPY IS?

12:43.197 --> 12:44.764
-WELL, THERE'S ONLY
THREE PEOPLE THAT KNEW

12:44.894 --> 12:46.678
WHAT HAPPENED IN THAT
APARTMENT LAST NIGHT.

12:46.809 --> 12:48.768
-DON'T LOOK AT ME, I MEAN,
I DIDN'T TELL ANYBODY.

12:48.898 --> 12:50.944
-AND IT COULDN'T BE CODY,
HE HATES ROGER PELTON.

12:51.596 --> 12:52.772
-GUESS WHO THAT LEAVES?

12:52.902 --> 12:54.121
-LANI: J.D.

12:54.251 --> 12:57.646
[ROCK MUSIC]

12:57.777 --> 13:00.083
-RIPTIDE: THIS IS
RIPTIDE ROGER PELTON,

13:00.214 --> 13:01.781
AND THERE HE IS,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

13:01.911 --> 13:06.350
THE BOLD AND BODACIOUS
MICHAEL "THE STUD" NEWMAN!

13:09.571 --> 13:12.095
BEING DRIVEN TO WORK
BY HIS LOVE GODDESS.

13:12.748 --> 13:14.445
THEM, THERE.
WHAT'D I TELL YOU?

13:14.576 --> 13:16.926
DOES CHANTAL GOT
THE GREATEST LIPS

13:17.057 --> 13:19.233
YOU HAVE EVER
SEEN IN YOUR LIFE?

13:19.363 --> 13:21.975
I WOULD KILL TO BE KISSED BY
THOSE LIPS, LOOK AT NEWMAN!

13:22.105 --> 13:24.629
HE'S ACTUALLY TRYING
TO GET OUT OF THE CAR?

13:24.760 --> 13:26.980
WHAT KIND OF A
MORON IS THIS GUY?

13:28.111 --> 13:31.027
IF I WERE IN HIS SHOES,
I'D NEVER COME TO WORK!

13:31.158 --> 13:33.464
-OH YOU GUYS, I CANNOT WAIT
TO BE ASSIGNED TO A TOWER.

13:33.595 --> 13:34.857
I'M GONNA ASK MITCH
FOR BREAKWATER.

13:34.988 --> 13:36.337
THAT WAS
STEPHANIE'S FAVORITE.

13:36.467 --> 13:37.860
-THE SURF POUNDS OUT
THERE, AND THERE'S

13:37.991 --> 13:39.296
ALWAYS DANGEROUS RIPS
AROUND THE ROCKS.

13:39.427 --> 13:41.037
-I KNOW THAT, THAT'S
WHY SHE LOVED IT.

13:41.168 --> 13:43.083
SHE LOVED TO BE
WHERE THE ACTION IS.

13:43.213 --> 13:45.607
IT'S DEFINITELY WHERE I WANNA
BE, WHERE THE SURF POUNDS.

13:45.737 --> 13:47.609
-MITCH DOESN'T
ASSIGN TOWERS ANYMORE.

13:48.784 --> 13:50.568
LIEUTENANT WALSH DOES.

13:54.485 --> 13:59.447
-[UPBEAT GUITAR MUSIC]

14:17.465 --> 14:20.337
♪ I KNOW THERE MUST BE MORE THAN THIS

14:20.468 --> 14:23.036
♪ BUT LIFE CAN BE SO HIT OR MISS

14:23.166 --> 14:28.519
♪ I WANT TO BE RUNNING WILD
AND RUNNING FREE ♪

14:28.650 --> 14:31.783
♪ I WANT TO BUILD MY WAY UP TO THE TOP

14:31.914 --> 14:34.612
♪ HOLDING ON TO ALL I'VE GOT

14:34.743 --> 14:39.356
♪ FEELING SO SECURE IN MY DESTINY

14:40.314 --> 14:45.972
♪ ALL I KNOW IS LIFE'S A JOURNEY

14:46.102 --> 14:48.409
♪ GIVE ME A CHANCE
BEFORE THE DAY IS OVER ♪

14:48.539 --> 14:51.586
♪ I'M SO MUCH WISER
AND SO MUCH BOLDER ♪

14:51.716 --> 14:57.200
♪ GIVE ME A CHANCE
TO PROVE MYSELF TO YOU ♪

14:57.331 --> 14:59.550
♪ GIVE ME A CHANCE
TO SHOW YOU WHO I AM ♪

14:59.681 --> 15:02.510
♪ I'VE GOT A LOT TO LEARN
BUT I KNOW I CAN ♪

15:02.640 --> 15:07.602
♪ DO ANYTHING- I'LL PROVE MYSELF TO YOU

15:31.843 --> 15:35.673
-MITCH! HEY! HI!

15:35.804 --> 15:39.068
-GOD, I MISSED YOU!
HANG ON, HANG ON.

15:39.199 --> 15:40.156
NO HUGS ON DUTY.

15:40.287 --> 15:42.506
-OH RIGHT, SORRY, SORRY.

15:42.637 --> 15:43.986
SO HOW DID YOUR
COMMITTEE MEETING GO?

15:44.117 --> 15:46.554
-I HAD TO PINCH
MYSELF TO STAY AWAKE.

15:46.684 --> 15:48.991
-THE PRICE YOU PAY
FOR BECOMING CAPTAIN.

15:49.122 --> 15:51.385
GOD! LOOK AT YOU, YOU
BIG STUD! YOU LOOK GREAT!

15:51.515 --> 15:54.301
-WELL, STILL GETTING USED TO
WEARING A TIE ON THE BEACH.

15:54.431 --> 15:56.129
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
WHY DON'T YOU COME OVER

15:56.259 --> 15:57.826
TO THE HOUSE TONIGHT,
I'LL COOK YOU DINNER,

15:57.957 --> 15:59.654
WE'LL CATCH UP ON EVERYTHING,
INCLUDING THE HUGS.

15:59.784 --> 16:01.395
-OKAY, BUT ONE NIGHT
WON'T BE ENOUGH.

16:01.525 --> 16:02.570
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

16:02.700 --> 16:04.137
-[CAROLINE LAUGHS]

16:04.267 --> 16:05.747
-WELL, YOU CAN TAKE THE
CAPTAIN OFF THE SAND,

16:05.877 --> 16:07.575
BUT YOU CAN'T KEEP THE
SAND OFF OF HIS TOES.

16:07.705 --> 16:10.012
-GOT THAT! LISTEN,
YOU EVER SEE ME WEARING

16:10.143 --> 16:11.796
THESE CRAB STOMPERS
ON THE BEACH,

16:11.927 --> 16:13.624
SHOOT ME IN THE LEG,
PUT ME OUT OF MY MISERY.

16:13.755 --> 16:16.105
-OKAY, ONLY IF YOU PUT ME
OUT OF MY MISERY FIRST, MITCH.

16:16.236 --> 16:17.715
PLEASE, YOU GOTTA GET
ME OFF THIS BEACH!

16:17.846 --> 16:19.979
COME ON, EVERYTHING
IS GOING ON OUT THERE

16:20.109 --> 16:21.850
AND THAT NEW LIEUTENANT,
WHAT'S HER NAME? TAYLOR...

16:21.981 --> 16:23.156
-MITCH: WALSH.
-CAROLINE: YEAH.

16:23.286 --> 16:24.548
COME ON, SHE
STUCK ME OUT HERE.

16:24.679 --> 16:26.637
-CAROLINE, IT'S
YOUR FIRST DAY BACK,

16:26.768 --> 16:28.378
LIEUTENANT WALSH JUST
WANTS TO MAKE SURE YOU

16:28.509 --> 16:30.772
GET YOUR FEET WET HERE
ON MOTHER'S BEACH.

16:30.902 --> 16:33.035
-MITCH, THAT'S THE ONLY
THING I CAN GET WET HERE.

16:33.166 --> 16:35.864
COME ON! HEY! YOU'RE THE
CAPTAIN, OVERRIDE HER.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.387
-I'M THE CAPTAIN,
LIEUTENANTS GIVE OUT

16:37.518 --> 16:39.781
THE TOWER ASSIGNMENTS,
I CAN'T CHANGE A BEACH.

16:39.911 --> 16:41.522
-MITCH, THIS ISN'T
EVEN THE OCEAN HERE!

16:41.652 --> 16:43.132
COME ON, IT'S FOR ROOKIES.

16:44.133 --> 16:45.352
-HOLD ON A SECOND.

16:46.309 --> 16:48.050
-DISPATCH: WE HAVE A
CAPSIZED SAIL BOAT CAUGHT IN

16:48.181 --> 16:50.705
THE SURFLINE, DRIFTING TOWARD
DEL REY PENINSULA BEACH.

16:50.835 --> 16:52.707
SOS REPORTED FOUR
PEOPLE ON BOARD.

16:52.837 --> 16:55.188
-LIFEGUARD: WITH JET ONE,
EN ROUTE FROM VENICE PIER.

16:55.318 --> 16:57.233
-HEY, I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT
AT SEVEN, I GOTTA GO!

16:57.364 --> 16:58.713
-WELL WAIT, LET
ME COME WITH YOU!

16:58.843 --> 17:00.584
-YOU CAN'T LEAVE
THE BEACH UNGUARDED,

17:00.715 --> 17:02.151
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT
AT SEVEN, RELAX.

17:03.196 --> 17:05.023
-FINE. IT'S NOT FAIR!

17:06.676 --> 17:07.722
-LIFE ISN'T FAIR!

17:09.070 --> 17:13.989
-[INTENSE ROCK MUSIC]

17:30.832 --> 17:35.141
-[SIREN]

17:46.891 --> 17:49.198
-[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

17:49.329 --> 17:50.678
-LANI: COP CAR ON APPROACH.

17:50.808 --> 17:52.288
THREE VICTIMS COMING
OUT OF THE WATER,

17:52.419 --> 17:53.811
ONE APPEARS TO
BE UNCONSCIOUS.

18:05.214 --> 18:06.476
-THE MAST HIT HIM IN THE HEAD!

18:06.607 --> 18:07.347
-HE'S NOT BREATHING.

18:07.477 --> 18:08.870
-NO PULSE.

18:09.000 --> 18:09.958
-WE DON'T KNOW WHAT
HAPPENED TO RAMONA.

18:10.089 --> 18:11.829
-LANI: WAS SHE BELOW DECK?

18:11.960 --> 18:13.527
-FEMALE VICTIM: NO, SHE WAS
ON BOARD WHEN WE WENT OVER!

18:13.657 --> 18:15.224
-START CPR.

18:16.269 --> 18:20.360
ONE! TWO! THREE! FOUR! FIVE!

18:20.490 --> 18:21.622
-WAKE UP, PLEASE WAKE UP!

18:21.752 --> 18:24.625
-ONE! TWO! THREE! FOUR! FIVE!

18:24.755 --> 18:26.670
-RIPTIDE: RIPTIDE ROGER
PELTON, OVER THE SCENE OF

18:26.801 --> 18:28.716
A SAILBOAT CAPSIZED
NEAR SHORE.

18:28.846 --> 18:32.720
OKAY, LET'S SEE WHO WE'VE
GOT RESPONDING HERE...

18:34.287 --> 18:36.985
LOOKS LIKE LANI AND
J.D. ON THE BEACH,

18:37.116 --> 18:40.597
TENDING TO A VICTIM, AND
NEWMAN AND CODY HOT-DOGGING

18:40.728 --> 18:43.557
TO SHORE WITH A COUPLE OF
WAVERUNNERS, THIS IS GREAT.

18:43.687 --> 18:46.429
I'M GONNA BE ABLE TO PUT
YOU RIGHT OVER GROUND ZERO.

18:46.560 --> 18:49.171
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

18:49.302 --> 18:51.739
-[JETSKI ENGINES REVVING]

18:51.869 --> 18:54.394
-J.D.: ONE! TWO!
THREE! FOUR! FIVE!

18:54.524 --> 18:56.396
THERE'S ONE MISSING
IN THE WATER!

19:03.098 --> 19:04.447
-RIPTIDE: CODY AND
NEWMAN ARE IN THE WATER,

19:04.578 --> 19:06.275
APPARENTLY LOOKING
FOR ANOTHER VICTIM.

19:06.928 --> 19:08.364
-GET OUT!

19:10.279 --> 19:13.891
-THREE! FOUR! FIVE!
COME ON! ONE! TWO!

19:14.022 --> 19:17.025
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

19:17.156 --> 19:19.506
-RIPTIDE: VERY IMPRESSIVE.
YOU GOTTA HAND IT

19:19.636 --> 19:21.595
TO 'EM, THESE GUYS
ARE PROS AT THIS.

19:21.725 --> 19:25.251
LOOK AT LANI AND
J.D., STRUGGLING TO
SAVE THAT GUY'S LIFE.

19:25.381 --> 19:26.991
NO WONDER THESE
LIFEGUARDS ARE

19:27.122 --> 19:28.515
ALL OVER EACH
OTHER AFTER WORK.

19:29.472 --> 19:31.213
-DISPATCH: WE HAVE A
REPORT OF A NEWS HELICOPTER

19:31.344 --> 19:33.955
HINDERING THE RESCUE
OPERATION, PLEASE ADVISE.

19:35.826 --> 19:39.134
-NOW LISTEN, GET THE
COAST GUARD, THE AIR FORCE,

19:39.265 --> 19:41.745
A SWAT TEAM, I DON'T CARE,
I WANT THE HELICOPTER

19:41.876 --> 19:44.313
AT LEAST 100 YARDS
FROM THE RESCUE SCENE!

19:47.229 --> 19:48.839
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

19:48.970 --> 19:50.276
-CODY: I CAN'T FIND ANYONE!

19:50.406 --> 19:53.409
-[INTENSE MUSIC]

19:54.367 --> 19:55.890
-NEWMIE!
-WHAT?

19:56.673 --> 19:58.458
-UNDER THE SAIL!

19:58.588 --> 19:59.850
-OKAY!

19:59.981 --> 20:02.288
-I'LL GET THE MAINSAIL.

20:02.418 --> 20:03.811
-I'LL TAKE THE JIB!

20:06.335 --> 20:08.772
-GO ON, GET OUT OF HERE!

20:08.903 --> 20:12.167
-WELL, LOOK AT HIM! TRYING
TO USE ME AS AN EXCUSE

20:12.298 --> 20:14.909
FOR NOT STRIPPING OFF
HIS CAPTAIN'S UNIFORM

20:15.039 --> 20:18.129
AND PROVING THAT HE CAN'T
CUT IT IN THE WATER ANYMORE!

20:19.435 --> 20:20.523
-DAMN IT!

20:20.654 --> 20:22.743
-FOUR! FIVE!

20:22.873 --> 20:26.921
ONE! TWO! THREE!
FOUR! FIVE! COME ON!

20:27.704 --> 20:28.879
-[VICTIM COUGHS]

20:29.010 --> 20:30.359
-FEMALE VICTIM: OH, THANK GOD!

20:30.490 --> 20:31.447
-HE'S BREATHING, I'M
GONNA GO HELP MITCH.

20:31.578 --> 20:32.579
-LANI: OKAY.

20:32.709 --> 20:36.713
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

20:37.801 --> 20:39.455
-RIPTIDE: NOW LET'S GET
DOWN A LITTLE LOWER HERE,

20:39.586 --> 20:40.848
AND SEE WHAT WE CAN SEE.

20:41.892 --> 20:45.244
-[ROCK MUSIC]

20:51.337 --> 20:55.036
-[LIFEGUARDS GRUNTING]

21:09.790 --> 21:11.792
-GO! GET OUT!

21:14.360 --> 21:15.709
-OH MY GOD!

21:15.839 --> 21:21.454
-[INTENSE ROCK MUSIC]

21:26.415 --> 21:27.851
-GIVE ME A PADDLEBOARD!

21:27.982 --> 21:29.679
-GET A PADDLEBOARD IN HERE!

21:31.638 --> 21:33.727
-SHE MAY HAVE A BACK INJURY.

21:33.857 --> 21:36.686
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

21:42.083 --> 21:43.998
-[SIREN]

21:50.787 --> 21:56.010
-[HEAVY BREATHING
AND GRUNTING]

22:01.755 --> 22:03.713
-ALL RIGHT. GET
HER TO THE HOSPITAL.

22:04.453 --> 22:06.281
LET ME KNOW HOW
SHE IS, WILL YOU?

22:07.848 --> 22:08.849
GO ON!

22:10.285 --> 22:13.636
-[SIREN]

22:17.684 --> 22:22.689
-[ROCK MUSIC]

22:31.393 --> 22:33.830
-[PLEASANT JAZZ MUSIC]

22:33.961 --> 22:35.354
-I CALLED CHANNEL
10, I TOLD THEM THAT

22:35.484 --> 22:37.094
IF THEY DIDN'T FIRE
THIS GUY, I'M GONNA CALL

22:37.225 --> 22:40.054
EVERY SPONSOR,
THE FAA, THE FCC--

22:40.184 --> 22:41.577
-I KNOW, I KNOW.

22:41.708 --> 22:43.405
CODY SAID HE'D NEVER
SEEN YOU QUITE SO ANGRY.

22:43.536 --> 22:46.234
-THIS RIPTIDE GUY IS VERY
LUCKY THAT GIRL PULLED THROUGH,

22:46.365 --> 22:48.062
IF NOT, I'D HAVE
KNOCKED HIS HEAD OFF--

22:48.192 --> 22:50.281
-LOOK, LOOK! THE GOOD THING
IS HE'S OFF THE BEACH, OKAY?

22:50.412 --> 22:51.805
-OKAY.

22:51.935 --> 22:53.589
-HE CAN'T START ANY MORE
VICIOUS RUMORS ABOUT US.

22:53.720 --> 22:55.591
WHO DO YOU THINK
THE BAYWATCH SPY IS?

22:55.722 --> 22:58.333
-I DON'T KNOW. WHEN I FIND
OUT, I'LL FIRE THEM, TOO.

22:58.464 --> 22:59.987
-[CAROLINE LAUGHS]

23:00.117 --> 23:02.816
-WELL, SINCE YOU'RE ON
THIS WONDERFUL FIRING KICK,

23:02.946 --> 23:04.208
HOW ABOUT GIVING
LIEUTENANT WALSH

23:04.339 --> 23:05.993
THE BOOT AND
GIVING ME HER JOB?

23:06.123 --> 23:08.169
-SINCE WHEN DID YOU WANT TO
BECOME A CAREER LIFEGUARD?

23:08.299 --> 23:09.649
-SINCE I FIGURED
OUT IT'S PROBABLY

23:09.779 --> 23:11.302
THE ONLY CAREER
OPTION I HAVE LEFT.

23:11.433 --> 23:12.956
-WHAT HAPPENED IN NEW YORK?

23:13.087 --> 23:14.610
I THOUGHT YOU WENT
THERE TO DO BROADWAY,

23:14.741 --> 23:16.960
TO BE A SOAP STAR, I
MEAN, RETURN TO CALIFORNIA

23:17.091 --> 23:18.701
THE TRIUMPHANT MOVIE STAR.

23:18.832 --> 23:20.050
-YEAH. REALLY
TRIUMPHANT, ALL THE WAY

23:20.181 --> 23:21.878
BACK TO CALIFORNIA
ON A BUS, UGH!

23:22.009 --> 23:23.793
MITCH, IT WAS AWFUL.

23:23.924 --> 23:25.578
-WHAT HAPPENED?

23:25.708 --> 23:27.101
-I GET THIS GREAT AUDITION
FOR SHANNON'S HOPE, RIGHT?

23:27.231 --> 23:28.798
NEW CHARACTER, SOPHIA
THE ITALIAN HEIRESS.

23:28.929 --> 23:31.888
I GO IN THERE,
MITCH, I AM SOPHIA.

23:32.019 --> 23:34.151
IN THE MIDDLE OF MY AUDITION,
THE PRODUCERS START TO LAUGH.

23:34.282 --> 23:36.371
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE THIS
SERIOUS, EMOTIONAL SCENE

23:36.502 --> 23:37.851
AND THE PRODUCERS
ARE CRACKING UP!

23:37.981 --> 23:39.374
-[MITCH LAUGHS]

23:39.505 --> 23:40.767
SO AT THE END OF MY
AUDITION, THEY SAY,

23:40.897 --> 23:42.464
"THANK YOU FOR BREAKING
UP THE MONOTONY,

23:42.595 --> 23:44.466
"BUT BASICALLY, DON'T
CALL US, WE'LL CALL YOU."

23:44.597 --> 23:46.686
-I'M SURE
YOU'RE EXAGGERATING.

23:46.816 --> 23:48.775
-I WISH I WAS. I THINK
IT WAS THE DEFINING

23:48.905 --> 23:50.777
MOMENT OF HUMILIATION
IN MY LIFE.

23:50.907 --> 23:54.433
-CAROLINE, YOU CAN'T LET
ONE AUDITION KILL YOUR DREAM.

23:55.738 --> 23:57.479
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
MY DREAM IS ANYMORE.

23:57.610 --> 23:59.829
THE ENTIRE BUS RIDE
BACK, I KEPT ON THINKING,

23:59.960 --> 24:02.005
"WHAT WOULD STEPHANIE
WANT ME TO DO?"

24:02.136 --> 24:04.007
-YOU NEVER LISTENED
TO YOUR SISTER.

24:04.138 --> 24:05.531
-I KNOW, IT'S MY
PROBLEM, IF I HAD,

24:05.661 --> 24:07.663
I WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN
IN SO MUCH TROUBLE.

24:07.794 --> 24:10.666
-STEPHANIE WOULD TELL
YOU TO FOLLOW YOUR HEART.

24:12.146 --> 24:14.365
-I REALLY WANT TO BE AS GOOD
A LIFEGUARD AS STEPHANIE WAS.

24:14.496 --> 24:16.498
-THAT'S GONNA BE TOUGH.

24:16.629 --> 24:18.413
SHE WAS ONE OF A KIND.

24:18.544 --> 24:22.548
BUT, IF ANYBODY CAN BE
AS GOOD AS HER, YOU CAN.

24:24.724 --> 24:27.640
-SO, DOES THIS MEAN I'LL BE
WORKING BREAKWATER TOMORROW?

24:27.770 --> 24:29.729
-WHY DO YOU KEEP
ASKING ME THAT?

24:29.859 --> 24:32.383
I DON'T DO TOWER
ASSIGNMENTS. HEY HEY HEY!

24:32.514 --> 24:34.168
SAY THE SECRET WORD,
YOU WIN 100 DOLLARS.

24:34.298 --> 24:36.213
-[CAROLINE LAUGHS]

24:36.344 --> 24:37.998
-MITCH: WELCOME BACK.

24:38.128 --> 24:39.129
-[GLASSES CLINK]

24:39.260 --> 24:41.044
-COME ON, MAN. COME WITH US.

24:41.175 --> 24:42.698
-IT'S THE BEST CLUB IN LA!

24:42.829 --> 24:44.961
-J.D.: NAW, I'M
WIPED. YOU GUYS GO.

24:45.092 --> 24:46.006
I'M GONNA STAY
AND READ THIS.

24:46.136 --> 24:47.529
-WHAT IS THAT, A SCRIPT?

24:47.660 --> 24:49.052
-SHANNON'S HOPE.

24:49.183 --> 24:50.924
GAGE FALLS IN LOVE WITH
AN ITALIAN HEIRESS.

24:51.054 --> 24:54.362
-SOAPS ARE NOT AS MUCH FUN
AS REAL LIFE! COME WITH US!

24:54.493 --> 24:57.670
-AH, LET HIM STAY. WHO
NEEDS THE COMPETITION?

24:58.322 --> 24:59.976
-CODY: LATER.
-CHANTAL: BYE.

25:03.719 --> 25:05.329
-NEWMAN: OKAY, WHO'S DRIVING?

25:07.201 --> 25:11.945
-[SOMBER PIANO MUSIC]

25:36.143 --> 25:38.537
-OH, HI.
-HELLO.

25:39.450 --> 25:40.626
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING WITH THIS?

25:40.756 --> 25:44.020
-WHAT? OH, I FOUND
IT IN THE TRASH.

25:45.239 --> 25:47.154
THE SCENE WITH GAGE
IS REALLY GOOD.

25:47.284 --> 25:49.025
I LIKED THE WAY
YOU BROKE IT DOWN.

25:49.156 --> 25:50.679
-[CAROLINE SCOFFS]

25:50.810 --> 25:52.463
THESE ARE DARING CHOICES.

25:52.594 --> 25:55.379
-YEAH. SO DARING THAT
I DIDN'T GET THE PART.

25:56.424 --> 25:58.905
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT
BREAKING DOWN A SCENE, ANYWAY?

25:59.035 --> 26:02.256
-I STUDIED
ACTING IN COLLEGE. HEY!

26:04.519 --> 26:07.696
YOU CAN'T BURN THIS.
THIS IS SHANNON'S HOPE!

26:09.872 --> 26:11.091
HERE, SIT DOWN.

26:11.221 --> 26:13.006
-WHAT? WHAT FOR?

26:13.136 --> 26:14.050
-JUST SIT DOWN.

26:23.451 --> 26:25.235
-[J.D. SIGHS]

26:25.366 --> 26:27.760
-IT DOESN'T MATTER TO ME
HOW MUCH YOUR INHERITANCE IS.

26:27.890 --> 26:32.155
YOU COULD BE BROKE FOR ALL
I CARE. I'D STILL LOVE YOU.

26:32.286 --> 26:34.157
-[SCOFFS] WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

26:34.288 --> 26:36.290
-I'M GAGE! GO ON,
READ YOUR PART.

26:36.420 --> 26:37.726
-I DON'T HAVE A PART.

26:37.857 --> 26:39.293
-YES YOU DO, YOU'RE SOPHIA.

26:39.423 --> 26:41.425
DON'T THINK ABOUT IT,
JUST JUMP RIGHT IN.

26:41.556 --> 26:43.471
-WHY? SO YOU CAN
FEED MORE STORIES

26:43.602 --> 26:45.952
ABOUT ME TO RIPTIDE ROGER?

26:46.082 --> 26:48.694
-HEY! THAT GUY CALLED ME
THE DAYTONA PIER KILLER

26:48.824 --> 26:51.218
BECAUSE I LOST A
VICTIM THERE LAST YEAR.

26:51.348 --> 26:54.003
THE ONLY THING I'D FEED
HIM IS RAT POISON, OKAY?

26:54.134 --> 26:56.440
NOW, DO YOU NEED THE SCRIPT
OR DO YOU KNOW YOUR PART?

26:56.571 --> 26:58.573
-WHAT IS WITH YOU? WHY DO
YOU WANT ME TO DO THIS SO BAD?

26:58.704 --> 27:00.923
-BECAUSE, YOU
SHOULD ALWAYS GET

27:01.054 --> 27:03.099
BACK ON THE HORSE
THAT BUCKED YOU.

27:03.709 --> 27:04.971
[CAROLINE SIGHS]

27:07.713 --> 27:12.239
-[POUNDING DANCE MUSIC]

27:38.395 --> 27:40.267
-DJ: SOMEBODY SCREAM!

27:40.397 --> 27:42.922
-[DANCERS SCREAM]

27:43.052 --> 27:45.228
-NOW GET OFF MY DANCE FLOOR,
AND DON'T COME BACK

27:45.359 --> 27:49.319
UNLESS YOU THINK YOU
CAN KEEP UP WITH KYLA!

27:55.325 --> 27:56.239
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

27:56.370 --> 27:57.806
-IT'S A DANCE CONTEST.

27:57.937 --> 28:00.374
WHOEVER CAN KEEP UP WITH
KYLA THE LONGEST WINS.

28:00.504 --> 28:02.115
-WHO'S KYLA?

28:02.245 --> 28:03.986
-[THROBBING DANCE MUSIC]

28:04.117 --> 28:06.685
-[AUDIENCE CHEERS]

28:28.141 --> 28:29.925
-THAT'S LANI!

28:30.056 --> 28:31.579
-NEWMAN: YOU'RE
RIGHT! [LAUGHS]

28:33.059 --> 28:34.538
HEY, WHERE YOU GOING?

28:34.669 --> 28:35.975
-TO GET A BETTER VIEW, MAN.

28:36.105 --> 28:37.672
-[NEWMAN LAUGHS]

28:43.373 --> 28:45.114
-CONTESTANT 1:
MONEY, RIGHT HERE!

29:00.695 --> 29:02.131
-BOUNCER: YOU'RE DONE, PAL.

29:06.570 --> 29:08.877
-CONTESTANT 2:
HERE, I WANT SOME!

29:09.008 --> 29:10.444
-[AUDIENCE CHEERS]

29:59.188 --> 30:00.537
-CODY: HEY, LANI!

30:03.671 --> 30:06.761
SUP? I DIDN'T KNOW YOU
DANCED HERE! [LAUGHS]

30:09.111 --> 30:10.852
HEY WAIT, I WAS JUST
GONNA TALK TO HER!

30:11.418 --> 30:13.202
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL, I WAS
JUST GONNA TALK TO HER.

30:13.333 --> 30:15.596
-NOT UNLESS YOU PUT UP 10
BUCKS TO ENTER THE CONTEST!

30:15.726 --> 30:17.990
-CODY: YOU TAKE CHECKS?

30:18.120 --> 30:19.600
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

30:19.730 --> 30:21.776
-LAST TIME I FELT
THIS WAY, I WAS 16.

30:22.951 --> 30:24.953
IN LOVE WITH
MY BIOLOGY TEACHER.

30:26.215 --> 30:30.045
SHE REJECTED ME,
BROKE MY HEART.

30:31.612 --> 30:33.875
-WELL, I'M SURE
IT'S MENDED BY NOW.

30:35.485 --> 30:38.010
OH, YOUR HEART'S
BEATING SO FAST!

30:38.140 --> 30:39.925
-BECAUSE OF YOU.

30:40.055 --> 30:43.015
-OH, THAT MAKES ME HAPPY
TO KNOW THAT I EXCITE YOU.

30:47.584 --> 30:49.021
-DON'T BREAK MY HEART.

30:49.151 --> 30:54.026
-[ROMANTIC PIANO MUSIC]

30:59.031 --> 31:00.249
-[DOOR SLAMS]

31:01.424 --> 31:03.296
-SHOULD I COME BACK LATER?

31:03.426 --> 31:06.560
-NOPE. NO, NO. WE
WERE JUST REHEARSING

31:06.690 --> 31:08.997
A SCENE FROM SHANNON'S HOPE.

31:09.128 --> 31:12.131
SEE, I'M SOPHIA,
AND HE'S GAGE.

31:12.261 --> 31:15.830
-AND I'M STEVEN
SPIELBERG. [LAUGHS]

31:15.961 --> 31:17.049
-[DOOR OPENS]

31:18.833 --> 31:20.226
-[DOOR CLOSES]

31:20.356 --> 31:22.228
-IF ROGER RIPTIDE HEARS
ONE WORD ABOUT THIS,

31:22.358 --> 31:24.143
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT ME BREAKING YOUR HEART,

31:24.273 --> 31:25.840
BECAUSE I'M GONNA
BREAK YOUR LEGS!

31:25.971 --> 31:28.538
-[ROMANTIC PIANO MUSIC]

31:28.669 --> 31:30.279
-GOODNIGHT, SOPHIA.

31:30.410 --> 31:33.543
-[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

31:34.544 --> 31:37.765
-[UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC]

31:42.030 --> 31:43.162
-LANI, HEY.

31:43.292 --> 31:44.859
-LANI: HEY.
-CODY: WHOA!

31:44.990 --> 31:46.208
WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOU LAST NIGHT?

31:46.339 --> 31:47.949
-NOTHING, I JUST WENT HOME.

31:48.689 --> 31:49.864
-WE WAITED FOR YOU
TO COME BACK OUT.

31:49.995 --> 31:51.257
-I WENT OUT THE BACK WAY.

31:51.387 --> 31:52.998
-WHY? WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

31:53.128 --> 31:55.217
HOW COME YOU KEPT DANCING
THERE SUCH A BIG SECRET?

31:55.348 --> 31:57.176
-BECAUSE I DON'T
WANT RIPTIDE ROGER

31:57.306 --> 31:59.178
ANNOUNCING TO THE WORLD
THAT MY DANCE CAREER

31:59.308 --> 32:01.354
IS THE EQUIVALENT OF A
MECHANICAL BULL RIDING CONTEST.

32:01.484 --> 32:03.922
WHOEVER LASTS
THE LONGEST WINS.

32:04.052 --> 32:07.360
-WHY? THERE IS NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

32:07.490 --> 32:09.884
-YOU DON'T KNOW
THIS DANCE BUSINESS.

32:10.624 --> 32:13.627
-TAYLOR, CAROLINE DESERVES
TO WORK A MORE ACTIVE TOWER.

32:13.757 --> 32:16.151
-SHE'S BEEN OFF THE BEACH
FOR ALMOST SIX MONTHS NOW.

32:16.282 --> 32:18.240
BY ALL RIGHTS, I SHOULD HAVE
MADE HER WAIT UNTIL NEXT

32:18.371 --> 32:20.590
MONTH'S RECHECK BEFORE I
ASSIGNED HER TO A TOWER AT ALL.

32:20.721 --> 32:22.462
-MITCH: IF YOU'RE
INSECURE ABOUT HER ABILITY,

32:22.592 --> 32:24.246
PUT HER NEXT TO
NEWMAN'S TOWER.

32:24.377 --> 32:25.856
-TAYLOR: IS THAT AN ORDER?

32:25.987 --> 32:26.945
-NO.

32:28.772 --> 32:29.904
IF YOU THINK CAROLINE
NEEDS TO WORK

32:30.035 --> 32:31.732
MOTHER'S BEACH
THAT'S YOUR CALL,

32:31.862 --> 32:34.300
I AM OUT OF IT, IT IS
TOTALLY YOUR DECISION.

32:34.430 --> 32:35.779
-IS THAT MANIPULATION?

32:35.910 --> 32:37.259
-NO, NO! NOT AT ALL,
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,

32:37.390 --> 32:39.044
IF YOU DON'T THINK
SHE'S EXPERIENCED ENOUGH

32:39.174 --> 32:40.959
TO HAVE AN ACTIVE
BEACH, THEN THAT'S FINE,

32:41.089 --> 32:44.484
I MEAN, THAT'S
TOTALLY YOUR CALL.

32:49.706 --> 32:54.059
-[UPBEAT ELECTRONIC MUSIC]

33:07.681 --> 33:08.943
-HEY!

33:09.074 --> 33:10.814
-HEY, MITCH!

33:10.945 --> 33:12.033
-YEAH?
-DONNA: COME HERE.

33:12.164 --> 33:14.209
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE THIS.

33:17.778 --> 33:19.954
-NEWS ANCHOR: NOW, A NEW
FEATURE, OUR EXCLUSIVE

33:20.085 --> 33:21.129
EYE IN THE SKY REPORTER--

33:21.260 --> 33:22.609
-TELL ME IT'S A RERUN.

33:22.739 --> 33:24.654
-IT'S ON CABLE ACCESS.

33:25.307 --> 33:27.744
-I'M BACK!

33:27.875 --> 33:28.876
-DAMN IT.

33:29.007 --> 33:33.924
-[UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC]

33:41.062 --> 33:42.672
-WAIT FOR ME, I'M COMING!

33:45.327 --> 33:46.894
-COME ON, LET'S GO!

33:52.508 --> 33:54.293
-RIPTIDE: THIS IS
RIPTIDE ROGER PELTON,

33:54.423 --> 33:55.903
FLYIN' LEAN AND
MEAN OVER THE BEACH,

33:56.034 --> 33:57.992
NO MORE FANCY REMOTE
CAMERAS, JUST ARTIE,

33:58.123 --> 34:00.168
MY GOOD
OLD-FASHIONED CAMERAMAN.

34:00.299 --> 34:03.867
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

34:03.998 --> 34:06.653
LET'S SEE WHO
WE GOT DOWN HERE.

34:06.783 --> 34:09.656
WHY, IT'S LANI MCKENZIE!

34:09.786 --> 34:12.876
PLAY YOUR BOOMBOX REAL
LOUD AT LANI'S TOWER,

34:13.007 --> 34:14.617
MAYBE SHE'LL FORGET
WHICH JOB SHE'S AT

34:14.748 --> 34:17.141
AND DANCE FOR US RIGHT
HERE ON THE BEACH.

34:17.272 --> 34:20.232
OH, AND CALL HER
KYLA. THAT'S THE NAME

34:20.362 --> 34:22.408
SHE DANCES
UNDER AT CLUB RIO.

34:22.538 --> 34:23.974
WHO ELSE WE GOT
COMIN' UP HERE?

34:24.105 --> 34:25.802
IT LOOKS LIKE
CAPTAIN'S TRUCK.

34:26.934 --> 34:28.065
WHAT'S THE
DIFFERENCE BETWEEN

34:28.196 --> 34:30.590
MITCH BUCHANNON
AND A SEA TURTLE?

34:30.719 --> 34:32.766
WELL, A SEA TURTLE
RUNS FASTER ACROSS

34:32.896 --> 34:34.637
THE BEACH AND
KNOWS HOW TO SWIM!

34:41.775 --> 34:46.431
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

34:47.781 --> 34:49.565
-SHARK OFF TOWER 12!

34:54.222 --> 34:57.138
ATTENTION, ATTENTION!
EVERYBODY OUT OF THE WATER!

34:57.791 --> 35:01.186
PLEASE REMAIN CALM!
EVERYBODY OUT OF THE WATER!

35:05.842 --> 35:07.366
-WELL, LOOKS LIKE
WE GOT SOMETHIN'

35:07.496 --> 35:11.457
GOING ON UP AT TOWER 12,
AND WHAT DO YOU KNOW? WOW!

35:11.587 --> 35:16.549
LOOKS LIKE CAROLINE HOLDEN IS
BACK IN THE HEAT OF BATTLE.

35:16.679 --> 35:19.117
I'VE BEEN HEATIN' JUST
WATCHIN' HER, THAT'S FOR SURE.

35:20.683 --> 35:21.554
-ARTIE: I GOT SOMETHING.

35:21.684 --> 35:23.904
-WHAT?

35:25.210 --> 35:30.171
IT'S A SHARK! ALL RIGHT! I
LOVE THE RESPECT A SHARK GETS!

35:30.302 --> 35:34.132
MAN AGAINST MAN-EATER, I ASPIRE
TO THAT SAME KIND OF RESPECT.

35:34.262 --> 35:36.786
PEOPLE SEE ME COMIN'
AND START TO RUN.

35:36.917 --> 35:40.660
LET'S MOVE ON IN AND GET
A GOOD LOOK AT THIS BEAST.

35:42.879 --> 35:44.272
ARTIE!

35:44.403 --> 35:47.014
-[ARTIE SCREAMS]

35:59.374 --> 36:02.638
ARTIE! ARTIE, GRAB ON! ARTIE!

36:02.769 --> 36:06.076
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

36:06.207 --> 36:08.905
-[SIREN]

36:38.283 --> 36:42.069
ARTIE! ARTIE! GRAB THE STRUT!

36:55.125 --> 36:56.562
-[RIPTIDE GRUNTS]

36:57.911 --> 36:59.826
-[HELICOPTER CONTROLS BEEP]

37:01.306 --> 37:02.785
-[SPLASH]

37:02.916 --> 37:06.093
-[CONTROLS BEEP WILDLY]

37:11.707 --> 37:14.884
-[BEACHGOERS CLAMORING]

37:18.323 --> 37:19.759
-[ELECTRICAL POPS]

37:23.719 --> 37:25.330
MY HARNESS IS STUCK!

37:29.334 --> 37:32.250
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

37:39.692 --> 37:42.260
-[METALLIC CLUNK]
-[TAYLOR GRUNTS]

37:43.217 --> 37:44.262
-I CAN'T GET OUT!

37:45.306 --> 37:46.960
-[JETSKI REVVING]

37:52.139 --> 37:57.057
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

38:00.016 --> 38:02.236
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

38:02.367 --> 38:05.587
-[RIPTIDE GRUNTS]

38:20.123 --> 38:21.603
-LIFEGUARD: GOT
HIM! I GOT HIM!

38:27.305 --> 38:30.003
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

38:38.968 --> 38:44.104
-[GIRLS MOANING
AND SHOUTING]

38:50.850 --> 38:54.201
-[HEAVY BREATHING]

38:55.985 --> 39:00.686
-[RIPTIDE GRUNTING]

39:00.816 --> 39:05.038
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

39:41.422 --> 39:42.771
-YOU OKAY?
-CAROLINE: YEAH.

39:42.902 --> 39:47.863
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

39:57.264 --> 40:00.920
-[MITCH AND NEWMAN
GASP FOR BREATH]

40:07.230 --> 40:11.626
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

40:11.757 --> 40:13.106
-[RIPTIDE COUGHS]

40:13.236 --> 40:17.502
-OH MAN, I
THOUGHT I WAS DEAD.

40:17.632 --> 40:20.722
THOUGHT I ATE IT FOR
SURE. THANKS, MAN.

40:23.508 --> 40:25.379
I TAKE BACK EVERYTHING
I SAID ABOUT YOU.

40:25.510 --> 40:27.381
-I'M REGRETTING
THIS ALREADY.

40:29.688 --> 40:31.080
-CHANTAL: SWEETIE!

40:33.343 --> 40:34.649
HONEY!

40:36.129 --> 40:38.131
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
I WAS SO SCARED!

40:38.261 --> 40:39.524
-RIPTIDE: YEAH, I'M GOOD.

40:41.264 --> 40:43.397
-I WAS SO WORRIED ABOUT YOU!

40:46.531 --> 40:48.924
-MITCH: GUESS
WE FOUND OUR SPY.

40:49.055 --> 40:50.622
-I THINK I'M
GONNA BE SICK.

40:50.752 --> 40:54.277
-TELEPHONE,
TELEGRAPH, TELL NEWMIE.

40:55.235 --> 40:59.631
-HEY, I ONLY TOLD HER
THINGS OTHER PEOPLE TOLD ME.

40:59.761 --> 41:02.155
-LOOSE LIPS SINK SHIPS.

41:02.285 --> 41:03.461
-SHE WAS SO BEAUTIFUL.

41:03.591 --> 41:05.114
-AND BUOYANT.

41:09.815 --> 41:11.251
-THANK YOU, CODY.

41:11.381 --> 41:14.472
-AW, THANK CAROLINE.
SHE GOT TO YOU FIRST.

41:15.864 --> 41:17.692
I'M REALLY GLAD YOU'RE
BACK AT BAYWATCH.

41:17.823 --> 41:18.824
-SO AM I.

41:18.954 --> 41:23.959
-[PLEASANT MUSIC]

41:30.923 --> 41:33.447
-MITCH: MEET OUR
SPY, NEWMIE!

41:33.578 --> 41:35.405
-CODY: NEWMAN? IT WAS YOU?!

41:37.538 --> 41:40.367
NEWMIE! COME ON,
GET HIM, CAROLINE!

41:42.500 --> 41:47.243
-[END THEME PLAYS]
